    "objective": "“to examine and quantify the magnitude of PB interactions with other, concomitantly used, antiepileptic drugs via establishing population pharmacokinetic model for PB in adult epilepsy patients and to consider its use in individualization of PB dosing regimen”",
    "covariates": "Tested: SEX, comedication (LMT, TPM, CBZ, VPA), WT, AGE, serum creatinine, AST, ALT Included: VPA on CL; WT on Vd",
    "observations": "Neither WT nor PHB daily dose effect on CL, which is uncommon for PHB. A bias seems visible in the PRED vs DV plot, which may be the result of missing WT as covariate on CL. A linear relationship between daily VPA dose and PHB clearance was found, which allows more finetuning of dosing compared to regular on/off covariate effects of comedication, even if a linear relationship is improbable as the reduction of PHB CL by VPA would probably top off at a certain dose.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "1 compartment with first order absorption and elimination",
